({\it Regularity of the induced field of parallelepipeds.}) {\rm The one parameter fields of eigenvalues of the one parameter tensor field $\boldsymbol{q}(s)$ along a parametric curve $\mathcal{C}$ always posses the same regularity as that of $\boldsymbol{q}(s)$  \cite{laxbook, rellichbook}. If all the eigenvalues are simple throughout $\mathcal{C}$, then the corresponding field of eigenvectors has the same regularity as that of $\boldsymbol{q}$. This is also true if the multiplicity of all the eigenvalues remains constant throughout the curve. In case of isotropic metric anomalies, the multiplicity is 3 throughout $\mathcal{C}$; hence, the field of cubes has the same regularity as the function $\mu_{,k}(s)$ along $\mathcal{C}$.
 }
\end{rem}



